Executive Profile
Reese B. Pinney  Chief Operational Officer, Amazing Energy Oil and Gas, Co.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships60--As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Reese B. Pinney has been Chief Operational Officer of Amazing Energy Oil and Gas, Co. since April 20, 2016. Mr. Pinney Co-Founded Gulf South Holding, Inc. in June 2008 and serves as its Senior Vice President. Mr. Pinney is responsible for all geological and geophysical evaluations. In 1992, Mr. Pinney co-founded Gulf South Operators, Inc. and has served as its President since 1992. He serves as an Executive Director of Gulf South Energy Partners 2013 LP. Mr. Pinney ... is responsible for all of Gulf South Holding’s geological and geophysical evaluations. Mr. Pinney is a petroleum geologist. In his 29 year career, Mr. Pinney developed extensive experience identifying and developing lower risk development drilling opportunities. He began his career in 1980 as an independent lease broker and worked closely with geologists to acquire mineral leases covering their drilling projects. In 1983, he began working at C&R Exploration, where he assisted in the development of trend plays in the Frio, Tuscaloosa and Cotton Valley Trends in Mississippi and the Frio and Cockfield Trends in southwest Louisiana. Mr. Pinney joined McMoRan Exploration in 1985, where he developed prospects in south Louisiana and Mississippi and supervised company interests for all wells in Mississippi, Alabama and Florida. He left McMoRan in 1986. He was an Independent Geologist and focused on the Miocene Trend in south Louisiana. He serves as Director of Gulf South Holding. Mr. Pinney serves as a Director of Rampart Energy, LLC and Lexington Resources Inc. He served as Director of Amazing Energy Oil and Gas, Co. since April 20, 2016 until February 4, 2017. He is an active Member of the Society of Independent Earth Scientists, New Orleans Geological Society and the American Association of Petroleum Geologists. He has an MS in Earth Sciences from the University of New Orleans in 1984. Mr. Pinney is a graduate of the University of Virginia with a BA in Economics and History.Read Full Background




